                            <comment id="17875170" author="JIRAUSER306156" created="Tue, 20 Aug 2024 12:34:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=frankvicky&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;frankvicky&quot;&gt;frankvicky&lt;/a&gt; Thanks for taking care of this! Making both `DefaultTaskExecutor::currentTask` and `DefaultTaskExecutor::runOnce` synchronized is a quick solution. However, I&apos;m not sure if this will introduce any performance regression. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=chia7712&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;chia7712&quot;&gt;chia7712&lt;/a&gt; I&apos;m currently running a concurrency testing tool that reruns all Kafka tests with different thread schedules. This helped me to find many bugs. While I can reproduce these failures and (sometimes) identify the root cause, I don&apos;t have enough context to fix these issues since I am not familiar with the codebase. Please let me know if you want me to report these bugs through another channel. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
